  <thing id="rRvnHlfVis" name="Half-Vistani" description="Half-Vistani (or {i}giogoto{/i}, in the Vistani patterna [see below]) are the result of a union between a Vistana and a {i}giorgio{/i} (any non-Vistani human). Unlike the other special races of Ravenloft, half-Vistani are entirely human. However, the traits they inherit from their Vistani blood separate them from normal men.\n\nLove affairs between {i}giorgio{/i} and the Vistani are often torrid and brief. The cultural rift cuts deeply, so precious few {i}giogoto{/i} ever grow up knowing both of their parents. Most often, the Vistana parent moves on in the night, abandoning the child to the {i}giorgio{/i}. Rarely, a {i}giogoto{/i} child is raised by the tribe of its Vistana parent. In either case, the child may be cared for but is never truly accepted. The {i}giogoto&apos;s giorgio{/i} family may fear that the child will develop the peculiar talents of her Vistani kin, and since the {i}giogoto{/i} is not fully &quot;of the blood,&quot; she finds herself unable to share entire worlds of Vistani experiences.\n\n{b}Personality{/b}: Broken homes are the {i}giogoto&apos;s{/i} birthright. Many spend their lives haunted by their youth; a rejected child often matures into a sullen and withdrawn adult.\n\nIt is no small matter to straddle the cultural rift of their birth, so most {i}giogoto{/i} choose to adopt one culture over the other. They either adhere to the customs of their homeland or wrap themselves in the Vistani mystique. Regardless of the heritage they favor, half-Vistani tend to be passionate and pessimistic individuals.\n\n{b}Physical Description{/b}: Half-Vistani resemble their Vistani parents, often inheriting their angular and aquiline features, eyes and hair of deep brown or black, and dusky or olive complexions. Of course, {i}giogoto{/i} often exhibit traits of their {i}giorgio{/i} heritage as well. A {i}giogoto{/i} can conceal her Vistani heritage, fooling {i}giorgio{/i} with a successful Disguise check (considered minor details only). Such tricks fail against true Vistani, however, who can identify those who are &quot;of the blood&quot; with but a glance.\n\n{b}Relations{/b}: {i}Giogoto{/i} are caught between two worlds; {i}giorgio{/i} treat them like Vistani, and the Vistani treat them like {i}giorgio{/i}. A {i}giogoto&apos;s{/i} outlook toward nonhumans usually mirrors that of his homeland. It is not uncommon, however, for half-Vistani to be more accepting toward other &quot;unwelcome&quot; creatures, such as Calibans and half-elves.\n\n{b}Alignment{/b}: In many ways, the {i}giorgio{/i} life mimics that of half-elves. Many half-Vistani spend their lives alienated from society and often grow to distrust authority. {i}Giogoto{/i} ethical alignment tends toward chaos, but they are no more inherently good or evil than any other humans.\n\n{b}Homelands{/b}: The Vistani endlessly wander throughout the Land of Mists, so a {i}giogoto{/i} may be born in any domain. The ruthless oppression of Vistani in Invidia makes native half-Vistani rare in that domain, while {i}giogoto{/i} are slightly more common in neighboring Barovia. No permanent half-Vistani communities exist anywhere in Ravenloft.\n\n{b}Religion{/b}: {i}Giogoto{/i} raised by {i}giorgio{/i} typically adopt the prevalent faith of their homeland. {i}Giogoto{/i} raised by the Vistani are seldom religious; the Vistani worship no gods and have many legends of their cruel mistreatment at the hands of godlike beings in the distant past. Some Vistani, particularly those of the Vatraska tribe, treat fate, the Mists, and the forces of nature with a respect that approaches reverence, however.\n\n{b}Language{/b}: {i}Giogoto{/i} have no language of their own, instead learning the domain languages of their homeland. {i}Giogoto{/i} who embrace their Vistani heritage often also learn {i}pattema{/i}, the Vistani&apos;s spoken language, and {i}tralaks{/i}, the Vistani system of trail symbols.\n\n{b}Names{/b}: {i}Giogoto{/i} raised by giorgio are often given names drawn from their homeland&apos;s cultures. {i}Giogoto{/i} raised by the Vistani are named in the Vistani tradition, and it is not unheard of for a half-Vistani raised by a {i}giorgio{/i} to be named after her wayward Vistana parent.\n\n{b}Vistani Male Names{/b}: Bela, Grigori, losif, Karol, Ludovic, Nicu, Pyotr, Simione, Stefan, Vasile.\n\n{b}Vistani Female Names{/b}: Ana, Eliza, Isabela, Lela, Natasha, Papusza, Rozalina, Sofya, Ursula, Yvonne.\n\n{b}Adventurers{/b}: Many {i}giogoto{/i} become wanderers, seeking happiness in foreign lands. Many fall in with other outcasts and eccentrics during their aimless travels.\n\n{b}Recommended Feats{/b}: Alertness, Ethereal Empathy, Lunatic, Track, Voice of Wrath.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Ravenloft Campaign Setting" compset="Race">
