  <thing id="gBookPrint" name="Book, Printed" description="The emergence of the printing press has allowed literature to flourish in advanced domains. Although print runs are usually low &#151; rarely more than one hundred copies &#151; authors can publish their works for eager audiences. A library in Ravenloft might include manuals written to teach complex skills or martial techniques, epic tales presented as adventurers&apos; memoirs, angst-ridden romance novels, or even the infamous {i}Van Richten&apos;s Guides{/i}. At Cultural Levels lower than 9, books must be scribed by hand and thus tend to be restricted to vital topics: legal tomes, historical records, or religious texts." compset="Gear">
